		<text>
		<body>
		<pb n="1"/>
		
		<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>St Thomas</placeName> <date>1 Nov 1847</date></p>
		<p><addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
		<p><placeName>Phila</placeName></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
		  <p rend="indent(2)">I recd your few lines [&#63;]<lb/> late with the Occident for <date>Oct</date> I thank<lb/> you for inserting our affairs.  The <date>Sep</date> No I<lb/> have not recd.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">On <date>Sunday</date> evening a Young man of<lb/> our Congregation born at <placeName>St Croix</placeName> was baptized<lb/> by the <persName>Revd Mr Brett</persName> a Dutch Reformed Minister<lb/> the parents of this Young man completely neglected<lb/> his Religious education&#44; he was but twice in<lb/> our Synagogue&#44; never adhering to any of our<lb/> forms &amp; publicly defamed the day of <date>Kipur</date> by<lb/> going to business&#44; as soon as I heard that he<lb/> was so inclined I used my evidences[&#63;] to prevent<lb/> him but he would not give me a hearing.  The<lb/> consequence is in happiness to his family &amp; which they<lb/> richly merit&#8212;This <persName>Mr Brett</persName> is pursuing<lb/> </p>
		
		<pb n="2"/>
		
		<p>a line of conduct that requires our utmost<lb/> vigilance to stem.  he seduces our lads<lb/> of 13 to 15 Years to become teachers to his<lb/> Sunday School&#44; he has now two with him<lb/> teaching the negro children&#44; the Catechisms<lb/> the Parent of one never sends him to our school<lb/> altho warned to do so&#44; the other came to <del>our</del><lb/> school &amp; because his attendance was irregular<lb/> &amp; his conduct what it should not be &amp; was admonished&#44; he was<lb/> permitted by those in whose care he is to Keep away&#8212;do me the favor to put in your paper<lb/> an article of warning to parents &amp; guardians<lb/> setting forth what they have to answer for by<lb/> the neglect of giving their children a Religious<lb/> education &amp; causing them to attend the Synagogue<lb/> make it strong as coming from you&#59; for I fear<lb/> that unless something is done to arouse their<lb/> feelings we will have repetitions of what has<lb/> passed&#44; for <persName>Mr Brett</persName> has very very persuasive<lb/> [&#63;].</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">My daughter will be married this day</p>
		

		<pb n="3"/>
		
		<p>week.&#8211;With best wishes I am yr Truly</p>
		  <p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">A Wolff</persName></p>

		<p>don&#39;t forget my [&#63;] [&#63;]&#44; &amp; [&#63;]<lb/> please in the article to urge Parents &amp; guardians<lb/> of children to send them to school&#44; many from<lb/> private [&#63;] &amp;c. Do not send&#44; point out<lb/> the impropriety</p>
		<p>On <date>Sabath</date> M[&#63;] of Tabernacle 7 of our young<lb/> people were confirmed by <persName>Mr Carillar[&#63;]</persName> the<lb/> Ceremony was very impressive below the names<lb/> <persName>Mrs Daniel Wolff</persName>&#44; <persName>Misses Miriam</persName> &amp; <persName>Rebecca Wolff</persName><lb/> <persName>Miss D. Contessios[&#63;]</persName>&#44; <persName>Miss DeMya</persName> <persName>Mr Alexander<lb/> Wolff</persName> &amp; <persName>Mr Jacob Benjamin</persName></p>
		

		<pb n="4"/>
		
		<p><addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
		</body>
